===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|behemoth|behemoth, bemoth}}, from {{der|en|LL.|behemoth}}, from {{der|en|he|בְּהֵמוֹת|tr=behemót}}. The Hebrew word is either:
* an intensive plural of {{m|he|בְּהֵמָה||tr=behemá|beast}}, from {{der|en|sem-pro|-}} (compare {{cog|gez|ብህመ|t=to be dumb, to be speechless}}, Arabic {{ar-root|ب|ه|م}}), or
* less likely, a borrowing of {{der|en|egy|*pꜣ-jḥ-mw|<hiero>pA-i-H-E1-mw</hiero>|tr={{m|egy|*pꜣ-jḥ-mw}}|hippopotamus|lit=the ox of the water}}, from {{m|egy|pꜣ||definite article}} + {{m|egy|jḥ||ox, cattle}} + {{m|egy|mw||water}} in a direct genitive construction; for the pronunciation, cf. the later Coptic descendants {{m|cop|ⲡ-}} + {{m|cop|ⲉϩⲉ}} + {{m|cop|ⲙⲟⲟⲩ}}.

